review_blob: (bottle March 2009, supermarket) Cloudy yellow with white head that last. Skunky acid smell, citric and kinda hopy floral. Taste is so citric that I can not recognize anything else, no malt or hops, little bitter aftertaste. High carbonation contribute to the acidic flavor. Maybe a contaminated bottle or really close to expiration date (90 days according to Colonos)

Bottled. Cloudy light amber color with short head. Slightly citric smell, malty with caramel and vanilla aromas. Sweet balanced flavor with soft toasty bitterness. Good bubbles. Drinkable unfiltered, bottled fermented ale.
